# HELP_SECTION: TIME_TOLERANCES
MAX_TIME_DELTA CONFIGURATION:
The max_time_delta setting controls timing constraints for pair blocks and pattern blocks.
It specifies the maximum allowed time (in seconds) between related events.

PRECEDENCE ORDER (highest to lowest):
1. Command line --max-time-delta: Overrides model and default settings
2. Block-level max_time_delta: Overrides model level setting for that specific block only
3. Model settings max_time_delta: Overrides the default for all blocks in the model
4. Default value: {DEFAULT_MAX_TIME_DELTA} seconds (hardcoded constant DEFAULT_MAX_TIME_DELTA)

USAGE BY BLOCK TYPE:
• Pair blocks: Maximum time between start and stop patterns
• Pattern blocks: Maximum time between sequential patterns (when explicitly set)
• Timeline blocks: Not applicable (timeline blocks collect all matches regardless of timing)

BLOCK_TIME_TOLERANCE CONFIGURATION:
Controls how far backwards in time the engine will search for the next
pattern. Handles log entries that are slightly out of chronological order
due to logging system timing variations, buffering, and write delays.

Default: 5.0 seconds (model level only)

PRACTICAL USAGE:
• Handles system-level timing variations (1-15 seconds typical)
• Higher values increase flexibility but may allow false matches
• Lower values increase precision but may miss valid patterns

PRECEDENCE ORDER (highest to lowest):
1. Command line --block-time-tolerance: Overrides model settings
2. Model settings block_time_tolerance: Overrides default
3. Default value: 5.0 seconds

SCOPE AND LIMITATIONS:
• Model-level only        : Set by command line or model settings
• No block-level override : Unlike max_time_delta, no block level support
• Small values recommended: 1-15 seconds typical

USAGE BY BLOCK TYPE:
• Pattern blocks: Tolerance for sequential pattern matching
• Pair blocks: Tolerance for start/stop pattern matching
• Timeline blocks: Not applicable (collect all matches)

TROUBLESHOOTING:
• Patterns found out of order: Increase block_time_tolerance
• False matches occurring: Decrease block_time_tolerance

EXAMPLES:
# Command line override (highest precedence)
lpmptool --max-time-delta 60 --block-time-tolerance 2.0 -m model.yaml

# Global setting affects all blocks in the model
settings:
  max_time_delta: 60
  block_time_tolerance: 5.0

# Block-level max_time_delta overrides global for that block only
blocks:
  - label: "Fast Service"
    file: "service.log"
    start: "Service starting"
    stop: "Service ready"
    max_time_delta: 10  # This block uses 10 seconds, others use global

# Real-world example: High-load system with delayed logging
settings:
  block_time_tolerance: 10.0  # System under load, allow more tolerance
