# HELP_SECTION: BLOCK_LEVEL_SETTINGS
BLOCK-LEVEL VS MODEL-LEVEL SETTINGS:
Block-level settings override model-level settings for that specific block only.
Model-level settings apply to all blocks unless overridden at the block level.

Supported at both levels:
- optional: Skip if patterns not found
- profile: Write per-block profile files
- max_time_delta: Maximum time between patterns (pair/pattern blocks only)

Model-level only:
- block_time_tolerance: Block sequencing tolerance
- timeline_patterns: Named pattern sets
# END_HELP_SECTION: BLOCK_LEVEL_SETTINGS

# HELP_SECTION: PRECEDENCE_RULES
SETTING PRECEDENCE RULES:
1. Command line arguments (highest precedence)
2. Block-level settings (for that block only)
3. Model-level settings (applies to all blocks)
4. Default values (lowest precedence)

Example precedence chain for max_time_delta:
Command line --max-time-delta > Block max_time_delta > Model settings max_time_delta > DEFAULT_MAX_TIME_DELTA
