1.  IDENTIFICATION:
    - label: Description for output
    - file: Target log file(s) with wildcard and compression support

2.  PATTERN DEFINITION:
    - patterns   : Sequential patterns for event timing (pattern blocks)
    - start/stop : Paired patterns for duration measurement (pair blocks)
    - timeline   : Event timeline patterns for chronological analysis (timeline blocks)
    - OR patterns: Alternative matches using array syntax

    Block type is automatically detected based on presence of the following
    block labels:
    - 'timeline' field      = timeline block
    - 'start'/'stop' fields = pair block
    - 'patterns' field      = pattern block (default)

    Notes:
    - A model typically specifies a number of blocks.
    - Mixed models can contain a combination of ‘pattern’ and ‘pair’ blocks.
    - Timeline models cannot have ‘pair’ or ‘pattern’ labels.
    - All blocks are processed chronologically regardless of type, producing
        a unified timeline with event markers (pattern blocks), duration
        measurements (pair blocks), and chronological event sequences
        (timeline blocks) in temporal order.


3.  BEHAVIOR CONTROLS:
    - optional    : Skip if patterns not found (block or model level, default: false)
    - profile     : Write per-block profile file (block or model level, default: false)
    - max_time_delta : Max seconds between patterns (block or model level, default: 45)
    - controller  : Controller-only block flag (block level only, default: false)

    BLOCK-LEVEL LABELS REFERENCE:
    All blocks support the following labels:

    REQUIRED LABELS:
    • label       : Description for output (string, required)
    • file        : Log file(s) to search (string or list, required)
    • Pattern definition (one required):
      - patterns  : Sequential patterns list (pattern blocks)
      - start/stop: Start and stop patterns (pair blocks)
      - timeline  : Timeline patterns (timeline blocks)

    OPTIONAL LABELS:
    • optional       : Skip if not found (boolean, default: false)
                       Supports model-level default, block-level override
    • profile        : Write per-block profile file (boolean, default: false)
                       Supports model-level default, block-level override
    • max_time_delta : Max seconds between patterns (integer, default: 45)
                       Supports model-level default, block-level override
    • controller     : Controller-only block flag (boolean, default: false)
                       Block-level only, no model-level support

    PRECEDENCE FOR OVERRIDABLE LABELS:
    Block-level setting > Model-level setting > Default value

4.  GLOBAL SETTINGS:
    - timing constraints: max_time_delta, block_time_tolerance
    - output control    : max_log_length, loops, start_date
    - timeline patterns : named pattern sets for timeline blocks
    - block defaults    : profile, optional

    MODEL-LEVEL SETTINGS REFERENCE:
    All settings are optional and specified in the 'settings:' section:

    TIMING CONSTRAINTS:
    • max_time_delta         : Max seconds between patterns (integer, default: 45)
                              Command line > model settings > default
                              Block-level can override for individual blocks
    • block_time_tolerance   : Time tolerance for out-of-order log entries (float, default: 5.0)
